(The IETF has successfully governed Internet standards for over 35 years) show newline
(through open processes, rough consensus, and running code. We adopt) show newline
(their model not from lack of imagination but from recognition of what) show newline
(works.[^h1]) show newline
() show newline
([^h1]: Historical: The IETF emerged from the ARPANET community in 1986.) show newline
(Its processes evolved through practice, not theory. "We reject kings,) show newline
(presidents, and voting. We believe in rough consensus and running code.") show newline
(— Dave Clark, 1992.) show newline
