(OUR PROCESS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The IETF process is thorough but obscure. We do our own thing.[^d1]) show newline
() show newline
([^d1]: Design: IETF processes evolved for Internet-scale coordination) show newline
(across thousands of participants. We're smaller, faster, more direct. We) show newline
(reference their norms, not their bureaucracy.) show newline
() show newline
(What we take from IETF:) show newline
() show newline
(  * RFC format — Document structure, numbering, required sections) show newline
(  * RFC 2119 keywords — MUST, SHOULD, MAY precision) show newline
(  * Security Considerations — Required in every specification) show newline
(  * Rough consensus — General agreement over voting) show newline
(  * Running code — Implementations validate specifications) show newline
() show newline
